# ALTERNATIVE (not recommended): pure `_redirects` same-origin proxy.
#
# This proxies /api/* to the tunnel using a 200 rewrite, WITHOUT a Pages Function.
# Caveat: Cloudflare Pages `_redirects` proxying to an EXTERNAL origin does not
# reliably forward authenticated POST / multipart bodies, so login and receipt
# upload can fail. Prefer the Pages Function (functions/api/[[path]].ts) — the
# active `_redirects` only does the SPA fallback.
#
# If you still want the pure-_redirects route, replace the active `_redirects`
# with the two rules below (order matters — /api first, SPA catch-all last) and
# set the tunnel host:

/api/*  https://api.example.com/:splat  200
/*      /index.html                     200
